(2, 1, 1, -3961, -3032, 'Adam is formed, made, created on Tishri 1, 3961 B.C. Gen. 1:26-27; 2:7.', 5, '!!! year of Adam', '2_adam_creation.jpg', 'The Creation of Adam', 'Willis, VA', 1, '2021-02-03 16:00:57', '<p>How did we arive at this dating for the creation of mankind? To accurately determine Biblical chronology (dates) one must have an anchor. A date that is set and historically documented. Then one can mathematically calculate forward and backward from that anchor date acording to what is stated in the Scriptures.</p> <p>Our anchor is the Babylon captivity (see 569 BC). The Babylonians kept very accurate records, especially concerning astronomical events. Most scholars agree with the Babylonian records regarding the dating of the 70 years of captivity. From there we count backward through the Kings to the reign of Solomon and the construction of the Temple. From that date it is 480 years backward to the exodus. Then we move backward 430 years to the calling of Abram. then we simply follow the years and dating of the people mentioned in the Old Testament untill we reach the beginning of Adam&rsquo;s 930 years of life.</p>'),
