(15, 4, 0, 26, 26, 'Baptism of Jesus Christ, Shebat 20, February 16, 27 AD (Luke 3:1-22) (see commentary on Luke 3:1).', 1, 'Jesus Christ is 30 years old', null, null, null, 1, '2022-03-12 01:35:17', '<p>1<sup>st</sup> Cleansing of the Temple, Nisan 10, April 13, 27 AD.<br /> Acceptable Year begins, Sivan 13, June 7, 27 AD.<br /> Jesus 30 years old, Tishri 1, September 20, 27 AD.<br /> Transfiguration, Tishri 10, September 29, 27 AD. (See commentary on Matthew 17:2).<br /> Feast of Tabernacles, Tishri 15-22, October 4-11, 27 AD.<br /> Feast of Dedication, Kislev (aka Chislev) 35 - Tebeth (aka Tevet) 2, December 13-20, 27 AD.</p>'),
(17, 1, 0, -1020, -980, 'David&rsquo;s accession year as King over Israel. David reigned for 40 years. (2 Samuel 2:1-7; 5:1-5). See commentary on 2 Samuel 5:3.', 2, 'David''s !!! year of reign as King.', null, null, null, 10, '2021-02-02 19:03:30', '<p>During the reign of David the civil and Regnal years (calendars) were switched so they began in Tishri. The sacred calendar remained starting in Nisan. David was 30 years old when he began to reign as King. (2 Samuel 5:3-5).</p>'),
