(160, 1, 0, -1135, -1117, 'The accession year of the Ammonite oppression which lasted 18 years. (Judges 10:6-9).', 7, '!!! year of the Ammonite oppression.', null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-08 21:34:24', null),
(161, 1, 0, -1117, -1111, 'Jephthah&rsquo;s accession year as Judge over Israel.<br /> He judged for 6 years (Judges 12:7).', 5, 'Jephthah''s !!! year as Judge.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-14 04:09:43', '<p>This is the 300<sup>th</sup> year (inclusive reckoning) since the area in the Trans Jordan was conquered by Israel in the 40<sup>th</sup> year of wandering in the wilderness. (Judges 11:26).</p>'),
(162, 1, 0, -1111, -1104, 'Ibzan&rsquo;s accession year as Judge over Israel.<br /> He judged for 7 years (Judges 12:8-9).', 3, 'Ibzan''s !!! year as Judge.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-14 04:10:08', null),
(163, 1, 0, -1104, -1094, 'Elon&rsquo;s accession year as Judge over Israel.<br /> He judged for 10 years (Judges 12:11-12).', 4, 'Elon''s !!! year as Judge.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-14 04:10:24', null),
(164, 1, 0, -1094, -1086, 'Abdon&rsquo;s accession year as Judge over Israel.<br /> He judged for 8 years (Judges 12:13-14).', 5, 'Abdon''s !!! year as Judge.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-14 04:10:55', null),
(165, 1, 0, -1086, -1046, 'The accession year of the Philistine oppression which lasted 40 years. (Judges 13:1)', 7, '!!! year of the Philistine oppression.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-14 04:11:42', null),
(166, 1, 0, -1084, -1084, 'Samson is Judge over Israel sometime during the Philistine oppression.<br /> He judged Israel for 20 years (Judges 15:20).', 2, null, null, null, null, 1, '2020-12-08 19:12:54', null),
(167, 1, 0, -1046, -1021, 'Samuel&rsquo;s accession year as Judge over Israel reckoned as starting in Nisan of 2016 AH, the spring of 1045 BC. He Judged Israel all of the days of his life (1 Samuel 7:13-15). Here ends the 40 years of Philistine oppression.', 2, 'Samuel''s !!! year as Judge.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-07 19:57:16', null),
(168, 1, 0, -1033, -1033, 'Saul becomes king and co-reigns with Samuel. Although Saul reigned as King while Samuel was a Judge, Saul&rsquo;s reign is only counted in the chronology as the 2 years he reigned solo after the death of Samuel. (1 Samuel 13:1). Saul&rsquo;s total time as King was about 20 years.', 4, null, null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-02 19:36:12', null),
(169, 1, 0, -1022, -1020, 'Samuel dies. Saul&rsquo;s accession year in sole reign as King of Israel. Saul reigns 2 years. (1 Samuel 13:1, 14).', 7, 'Saul''s !!! year of reign as King.', null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-24 18:33:57', null),
(170, 1, 0, -1020, -1020, 'Saul&rsquo;s death, before Tishri of 2942 AH..', 7, null, null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-02 19:39:48', '<p>Saul died before Tishri in a battle with the Philistines. The Philistines were invading as were the Amalekites. Thus the time would have been before Tishri (in the fall) so the armies could live off of the crops still in the fields and the edible wild plants. In addition, the Philistines had deployed their army on the Esdraelon Plain, the location where Sisera had been defeated when it rained (Judges 4). The Philistines would not have been foolish enough to deploy so late in the year to risk an early fall rain.</p>'),
(171, 3, 0, -1020, -1018, 'Ishbosheth&rsquo;s Accession year in rival contention with David for the Kingship of Israel. (2 Samuel 2:4, 10). The beginning of 2 years of civil war. See commentary on 2 Samuel 2:9.', 1, '~~~ years of civil war.', null, null, null, 10, '2021-02-02 19:06:42', '<p>Ishbosheth was Saul&rsquo;s son. After 2 years of civil war, Ishbosheth is killed (2 Samuel 4:5-7). David is crowned King by all of Israel. David&rsquo;s reign totaled 40 years (2 Samuel 5:1-4).</p>'),
(172, 1, 0, -1013, -1013, 'David moves his Capitol from Hebron to Jerusalem. (2 Samuel 5:5). See <a href="/export/library/Old_Testament_Chronology.docx">Old Testament Chronology</a>.', 5, null, null, null, null, 1, '2021-02-11 18:18:02', '<p>David changed the calendar (Civil/Regnal) to begin in Tishri (rather than in Nisan) after moving his capitol to Jerusalem. The religious or sacred calanders remained as they were, beginning in Nisan.</p>'),
(173, 1, 0, -980, -980, 'David dies at age 70.', 2, null, null, null, null, 1, '2020-12-06 21:37:25', null),
(174, 1, 1, -976, -969, 'Construction of the Temple begins in the month of Ziv (also spelled Zif) (second month) of Soloman&rsquo;s 4<sup>th</sup> year as King (1Kings 6:1, 37; 2 Chronicles 3:2), exactly 480 years after the Exodus.', 2, '!!! year of Temple construction.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-07 21:11:13', null),
(175, 1, 0, -969, -969, 'The Temple is completed in the 8<sup>th</sup> month (Bul) of the 11<sup>th</sup> year reign of Solomon. (1 Kings 6:38).', 5, null, null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-04 19:53:35', '<p>The Temple being a sacred matter, the counting of the years are according to the sacred calendar (Nisan to Nisan). The Temple took 7 years to build.</p>'),
(180, 1, 1, -883, -861, 'Ahab&rsquo;s accession year as king in Israel in the 38<sup>th</sup> year (non-accession counting) of Asa&rsquo;s reign as King in Judah and reigns for 22 years (1 Kings 16:28-29).', 4, 'Ahab''s !!! year as King of Israel.', null, null, null, 1, '2021-02-02 12:13:23', null),
(181, 1, 1, -882, -879, 'Jehoshaphat begins co-reigning as King of Judah with Asa. The co-reign lasts for 4 years. (1 Kings 22:42; 2 Chronicles 12:31).', 7, 'Jehoshaphat and Asa co-reign ~~~ years', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-07 21:29:17', '<p>Scripture says Jehoshaphat reigns for 25 years. The counting of the 25 years begins with the co-reign with Asa.</p>'),
(182, 1, 0, -879, -863, 'Jehoshaphat&rsquo;s accession year as sole King in Judah in the 41<sup>st</sup> (accession year counting) of Ahab. (1 Kings 22:41).', 7, 'Jehoshaphat''s !!! year ruling solely as King of Judah.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-07 21:30:02', '<p>Jehoshaphat reigns co-reign with 4 years with Asa, then reign solely as King for 15 more years and finally 6 additional years co-reign with Jehoram for a total of 25 years.</p>'),
(183, 1, 1, -863, -858, 'Jehoram begins a co-reign with Jehoshaphat as King in Judah.', 7, 'Jehoram and Jehoshaphat co-reign for ~~~ years.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-07 21:34:20', null),
(184, 1, 1, -863, -862, 'Ahaziah becomes King of Israel and reigns for 2 years. (1 Kings 22:51).', 4, 'Ahaziah reigns as king in Israel ~~~ years.', null, 'Ahaziah reign ~~~ years as King in Israel.', null, 10, '2020-12-07 01:36:33', null),
(185, 1, 1, -862, -851, 'Joram In the 2<sup>nd</sup> year of Jehroam and 18<sup>th</sup> year from the beginning of the sole reign of Jehoshaphat, becomes King of Israel and reigns for 12 years. (2 Kings 1:17; 3:1).', 4, 'Joram is King in Israel ~~~ years.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-07 21:35:05', null),
(186, 1, 1, -858, -851, 'Jehoram in the 5<sup>th</sup> year reign of Joram of Israel (non-accession counting) becomes sole King of Judah and reigns for 8 years (2 Kings 8:16, 17; 2 Chronicles 21:5).', 7, 'Jehoram is sole King in Judah ~~~ years.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-07 00:02:29', '<p>Because of the association of Judah and Israel when Jehoram of Judah married the daughter of Ahab, Judah now adopts the non-accession dating system for Jehoram, Ahaziah, Athaliah and Joash.</p>'),
(187, 1, 0, -851, -851, 'Ahaziah becomes King in Judah and reigns 1 year. He is killed by Jehu King of Israel.', 7, null, null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-07 21:39:28', '<p>Ahaziah (not the Ahaziah of Israel) became King of Judah the 12<sup>th</sup> year of reign (non-accession counting) of Joram, King of Israel (2 Kings 8:25, or the 11<sup>th</sup> year reign of Joram (accession counting system) (2 Kings 19:29). He reigned for 1 year. The apparent discrepency is due to the change from accession to non-accession counting systems. When Joram began ruling in Israel, Judah was in the accession system (thus the 11<sup>th</sup> year). Using the contemporary system of counting, an extra year is attributed/given. This &ldquo;discrepency&rdquo; actually documents the shift.</p>'),
(188, 1, 1, -851, -845, 'Athaliah becomes King in Judah and reign for 7 years. (2 Kings 11:1-4).', 7, 'Athaliahi''s !!! year as King of Judah.', null, null, null, 1, '2020-12-07 02:07:38', null),
(189, 1, 1, -851, -824, 'Jehu becomes King in Israel. He kills both Joram of Israel and Ahaziah of Judah. Jehu reigns 28 years. (2 Kings 9:24-28; 10:36).', 4, 'Jehu is King of Israel ~~~ years.', null, 'Jehu reigns ~~~ years as King in Israel.', null, 10, '2020-12-07 02:02:12', null),
(190, 1, 1, -845, -805, 'Jehoash (a.k.a. Joash) becomes King of Judah (non-accession counting) in the 7<sup>th</sup> year of Jehu. He reigns for 40 years. (2 Kings 12:1; 2 Chronicles 24:1).', 7, 'Jehoash''s !!! year as King of Judah.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-09 16:49:13', '<p>During the reign of Jehoash, Judah returns to the accession system of dating.</p>'),
(191, 1, 1, -823, -807, 'Jehoahaz becomes King of Israel in the 23<sup>rd</sup> year (non-accession counting) of Jehoash King of Judah. He reigns for 17 years. (2 Kings 13:1).', 4, 'Jehoahaz !!! year as King of Israel.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-09 01:25:36', null);
INSERT INTO `chronevent` (`id`, `sqn`, `onebased`, `beginyear`, `endyear`, `eventtitle`, `colorindex`, `tooltip`, `picfilnam`, `piccaption`, `location`, `lastedituserid`, `lastedited`, `longdesc`) VALUES
(192, 1, 0, -811, -811, 'Israel and Judah both begin to start dating events according to the accession year system. Israel&rsquo;s switch may be due to Assyrian influence within the Kingdom.', 2, null, null, null, null, 1, '2021-02-02 12:15:02', null),
(193, 1, 0, -808, -792, 'Jehoash&rsquo;s accession year as King of Israel and reigns for 16 years. (2 Kings 13:10).', 4, 'Jehoash''s !!! year as King of Israel', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-15 00:25:26', '<p>This occurs in the 37<sup>th</sup> accession system year of the reign of Jehoash, King of Judah</p>'),
(194, 1, 0, -1775, -1775, 'Death of Eber (Genesis 11:17).', 3, null, null, null, null, 1, '2020-12-07 17:15:09', null),
(198, 1, 0, -806, -777, 'Amaziah&rsquo;s accession year as King of Judah in the 2<sup>nd</sup> year of Jehoash (a.k.a. Joash) and reigns for 29 years. (2 Kings 14:1, 2; 2 Chronicles 25:1).', 7, 'Amaziah reigns ~~~ years.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-09 16:46:54', null),
(199, 1, 0, -791, -763, 'Jeroboam II begins his sole reign as King of Israel in the 15<sup>th</sup> year of Amaziah. He continues his reign for a total of 41 years. (2 Kings 14:23).', 4, 'The !!! year of Jeroboam II''s continued reign.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-17 20:34:30', '<p>Amaziah lived 15 years after Jehoash died. (1 Kings 14:17; 2 Chronicles 25:25).</p>'),
(200, 1, 1, -803, -792, 'Jeroboam II begins a co-reign with Jehoash in Israel.', 4, 'Jehoash and Jeroboam II co-reign for ~~~ years.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-15 00:27:02', null),
(206, 1, 0, -605, -563, 'Nebuchadnezzar&rsquo;s accession year as King in Babylon in the 3<sup>rd</sup> year of Jehoiakim (Daniel 1:1, 2) also recorded as the 4<sup>th</sup> year of Jehoiakim (Jeremiah 25:1, 2). See commentary on Daniel 1:1. Nebuchadnezzar besieges Jerusalem. This is the 1<sup>st</sup> of 4 carrying away&rsquo;s to Babylon.', 1, 'Nebuchadnezzar''s !!! year as king in Babylon.', null, null, null, 1, '2021-02-11 18:19:27', '<p>The differences in the dating of Nebuchadnezzar&rsquo;s accession is due to the different calendars being used. Daniel is using the Sacred calendar with the years beginning with Nisan while Jeremiah is using the Civil or Regnal calendar with the years beginning in Tishri. Reckoning the year beginning with Nisan puts Nebuchadnezzar&rsquo;s accession in Jehoiakim&rsquo;s 3<sup>rd</sup> year of reign (3356 AH or the spring of 605 BC), while reckoning the year beginning in Tishri, Nebuchadnezzar&rsquo;s accession is reckoned in Jehoiakim&rsquo;s 4<sup>th</sup> year of reign (3357 AH or the fall of 605 BC).</p> <p>See <a href="/export/library/Old_Testament_Chronology.docx">Old Testament Chronology</a>.</p>'),
(207, 1, 1, -605, -536, 'The 70 years of captivity begins (Jeremiah 25:11, 12).', 6, '!!! year of Judah''s captivity in Babylon.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-18 00:10:40', '<p>The captivity of Judah began with the removal of the people and Temple vessels from Jerusalem to Babylon (Daniel 1:2-4).</p>'),
(208, 1, 0, -598, -598, 'Jehoiachin&rsquo;s accession year as King of Judah. He reigns for 3 month&rsquo;s (2 Kings 24:8; 2 Chronicles 36:9). See commentary on 2 Kings 24:6.', 2, null, null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-03 19:00:34', null),
(209, 1, 1, -598, -562, 'Jehoiachin is imprisoned by Nebuchadnezzar (2 Kings 24:15; 2 Chronicles 36:9, 10). See commentary on 2 Chronicles 36:9.', 5, 'Jehoiachin''s !!! year of imprisonment.', null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-03 19:03:07', null),
(210, 1, 0, -598, -587, 'Nebuchadnezzar installs Zedekiah as King in Judah who reigns for 11 years (2 Kings 24:18; 2 Chronicles 36:11).', 4, 'Zedekiah''s !!! year as King.', null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-02 20:16:48', '<p>Nebuchadnezzar changed the name of Mattaniah (Jehoiachin&rsquo;s father&rsquo;s brother) to Zedekiah (2 Kings 24:17).</p>'),
(211, 1, 1, -589, -520, 'Jerusalem is attacked on the 10<sup>th</sup> day of the 10<sup>th</sup> month of the 9<sup>th</sup> year of Zedekiah&rsquo;s reign (2 Kings 25:1, 2). Here begins the 70 years of the indignation on Jerusalem and the cities of Judah (Zechariah 1:12).', 6, 'The !!! year of indignation on Jerusalem and Judah.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 19:30:19', null),
(212, 1, 0, -588, -588, 'Yahweh speaks to Jeremiah while he is shut up in the courtyard of Zedekiah&rsquo;s guard (Jeremiah 32:1-2).', 5, null, null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-24 20:37:15', '<p>These verses document that the 18<sup>th</sup> year of Nebuchadnezzar&rsquo;s reign in Babylon equaled the 10<sup>th</sup> year of Zedekiah&rsquo;s reign in Jerusalem.</p>'),
(213, 1, 0, -587, -587, 'The fall of Jerusalem (2 Kings 25:1-21). See commentary on 2 Kings 25:8.', 2, null, null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-18 00:22:16', '<p>On the 9<sup>th</sup> day of the 4<sup>th</sup> month of the 11<sup>th</sup> year of Zedekiah&rsquo;s reign in Jerusalem the walls of the city are breached (2 Kings 25:3-7).</p> <p>On the 7<sup>th</sup> day of the 5<sup>th</sup> month of the 11<sup>th</sup> year of Zedekiah&rsquo;s reign in Jerusalem the Temple is burned and destroyed (2 Kings 25:8-21). See commentary on 2 Kings 25:8.</p> <p>Zedekiah&rsquo;s 11<sup>th</sup> year begins with Nisan (Fall or Tishri) of 3375 AH coresponding with 587 BC. The 4<sup>th</sup> and 5<sup>th</sup> months of that year would occur in the winter of 586 BC/ 3375 AH near the beginning of Nebuchadnezzar&rsquo;s 19<sup>th</sup> year as King of Babylon.</p>'),
(214, 1, 0, -574, -574, 'Ezekiel 40:1, The 25<sup>th</sup> year of Jehoiachin&rsquo;s imprisonment is equal to the 14<sup>th</sup> year after the destruction of Jerusalem. See commentary on Ezekiel 40:1.', 3, null, null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-02 20:21:58', null),
(216, 1, 0, -569, -569, 'Astronomical observations occur during the 37<sup>th</sup> year of Nebuchadnezzar&rsquo;s reign.', 3, null, null, null, null, 1, '2022-09-01 11:58:01', '<p>The astronomical observations during the 37<sup>th</sup> year of Nebuchadnezzer are recorded on a clay tablet (VAT 4956) curated by the Vorderasiatisches Museum (Near East Museum), Berlin, Germany. The observations match those beginning in the spring of 568 BC or -567 astronomical. See <a href="http://www.adamoh.org/TreeOfLife.wan.io/OTCh/VAT4956/VAT4956ATranscriptionOfItsTranslationAndComments.htm" target="_blank">http://www.adamoh.org/TreeOfLife.wan.io/OTCh/VAT4956/VAT4956ATranscriptionOfItsTranslationAndComments.htm</a>.</p>'),
(217, 1, 0, -562, -560, 'Amel-Marduk&rsquo;s (Evil-merodach of 2 Kings 25:27) accession year as King in Babylon.', 3, 'Amel-Marduk''s !!! year reign as King.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 20:36:24', null),
(218, 1, 0, -562, -562, 'Jehoiachin is taken from prison in the 37<sup>th</sup> year of his imprisonment (2 Kings 25:27; Jeremiah 52:31).', 5, null, null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 20:38:47', null),
(219, 1, 0, -560, -556, 'Negal Shar Usur&rsquo;s accession year as King in Babylon.', 2, 'Negal''s !!! year as King.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 20:40:55', null),
(220, 1, 0, -556, -556, 'Labashi Marduk&rsquo;s Accession year as King in Babylon. He reigned for 2 months.', 3, null, null, null, null, 1, '2022-03-31 01:27:22', null),
(221, 1, 0, -556, -539, 'Nabonidus&rsquo; accession year as King in Babylon.', 5, 'Nabonidus'' !!! year as King.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 20:44:43', null),
(222, 1, 0, -539, -530, 'Cyrus enters Babylon and begins his accession year as King of Babylon. See <a href="/comm/daniel/11" target="_blank">commentary on Daniel 11</a>.', 4, 'Cyrus'' !!! year as King in Babylon.', null, null, null, 1, '2021-01-02 20:50:48', null),
(223, 1, 0, -538, -538, 'Cyrus&rsquo; proclamation for the captives to return to Jerusalem and rebuild the Temple of Yahweh (Daniel 9:1-2; Ezra 1:1-2:70).', 4, null, null, null, null, 1, '2021-01-02 20:49:52', '<p>Many of the captives return (49,697 persons plus their animals) to Jerusalem. In the seventh month of the year they rebuilt the altar and resumed the sacrifices and offerings and the observance of the feasts (Ezra 3:1-6).</p>'),
(224, 1, 0, -536, -536, 'Temple reconstruction begins in the 2<sup>nd</sup> month (Sacred calendar, the month of Iyar) of the 2<sup>nd</sup> year of their coming back to Jerusalem, the Spring of 3425 AH/536 BC (Ezra 3:8).', 3, null, null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-24 20:43:21', null),
(225, 1, 0, -531, -522, 'Cambyses&rsquo; accession year as King in Babylon. See <a href="/comm/Daniel/11" target="_blank">commentary on Daniel 11</a> .', 2, 'Cambyses'' !!! year as King of Babylon.', null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-03 19:59:46', null),
(226, 1, 0, -531, -521, 'Accusations are written and sent to Cambyses who orders the reconstruction of the Temple to stop (Ezra 4:6).', 3, 'Temple re-construction is halted for ~~~ years', null, null, null, 1, '2020-12-14 00:26:49', null),
(227, 1, 1, -522, -521, 'Two years of uprisings begin within the Persian Empire. Darius emerges triumphant.', 1, '!!! year of uprisings in the Persian Empire.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 21:40:48', null),
(228, 1, 0, -522, -521, 'Bardiya&rsquo;s Accession year as King in Babylon. See commentary on Daniel 11:2.', 7, 'Bardiya''s !!! year as King in Babylon.', null, null, null, 1, '2021-01-09 01:58:36', '<p>Bardiya, a.k.a. Smerdis by the Greeks. For more information on Bardiya, see <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bardiya" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a>. Bardiya may have been killed and was impersonated by Gaumata (Pseudo-Smerdis).</p>'),
(229, 1, 0, -522, -521, 'Uprisings continue, Nebuchadnezzar III&rsquo;s accession (see <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nebuchadnezzar_III" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a>), Darius&rsquo; accession, Nebuchadnezzer IV&rsquo;s accession (see <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nebuchadnezzar_IV" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a>) as kings in Babylon.', 5, 'Nebuchadnezzar''s IV''s !!! year as King.', null, null, null, 1, '2021-02-03 18:45:16', null),
(230, 1, 1, -521, -486, 'Darius emerges triumphant as King in Babylon. See commentary on Daniel 11:2.', 4, 'Darius''s !!! year reign as King in Babylon.', null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-16 01:07:07', null);
INSERT INTO `chronevent` (`id`, `sqn`, `onebased`, `beginyear`, `endyear`, `eventtitle`, `colorindex`, `tooltip`, `picfilnam`, `piccaption`, `location`, `lastedituserid`, `lastedited`, `longdesc`) VALUES
(231, 1, 1, -520, -515, 'Darius lifts the ban on the reconstruction of the Temple. The work resumes on the 24<sup>th</sup> day of the 6<sup>th</sup> month of the 2<sup>nd</sup> year of Darius&rsquo; reign (Haggai 1:14-15).', 3, '!!! year of resuming the work on the Temple.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-08 19:17:43', '<p>Haggai prophesies over a span of four months.</p>'),
(232, 3, 0, -520, -518, 'Zechariah begins to prophesy in the 8<sup>th</sup> month and again in the 11<sup>th</sup> month beginning with the 24<sup>th</sup> day (Zechariah 1:1, 7).', 1, 'The Prophet Zechariah.', null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-08 21:58:05', null),
(233, 1, 0, -518, -518, 'The prophecy of Zechariah in the 9<sup>th</sup> month beginning with the 4<sup>th</sup> day (Zechariah 7:1).', 1, null, null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 21:59:16', null),
(234, 1, 0, -515, -515, 'The Temple is completed on the 3<sup>rd</sup> day of the 12<sup>th</sup> month of the 6<sup>th</sup> year after resuming the work (Ezra 6:15).', 3, null, null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 21:48:30', null),
(235, 1, 0, -515, -515, 'Esther is made Queen of Babylon, wife to Darius in the 10<sup>th</sup> month of the 7<sup>th</sup> year of his reign as King (Esther 2:16, 17).', 4, null, null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 21:56:34', null),
(236, 1, 0, -519, -519, 'The feast of Ahasuerus (Darius) in the 3<sup><sup>rd</sup></sup> year of his reign as King (Esther 1:3).', 4, null, null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-08 21:20:31', null),
(237, 1, 0, -510, -510, 'Haman casts lots against Mordecai in the 12<sup>th</sup> year of the reign of Darius beginning with the first month (Nisan) to the 12<sup>th</sup> month (Adar) (Esther 3:7).', 7, null, null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 22:12:45', null),
(238, 1, 0, -510, -510, 'Haman plots to destroy the Jews (Esther 3:8-15) but the order for the destruction is reversed (Esther 8:1-17).', 1, null, null, null, null, 10, '2021-01-02 21:19:41', null),
(239, 1, 0, -509, -509, 'The Judean&rsquo;s enemies are destroyed (Esther 9).', 3, null, null, null, null, 10, '2020-12-13 22:16:57', null),
(240, 1, 0, -502, -502, 'The report of the welfare of the Judeans in Jerusalem and the condition of the city wall comes to Nehemiah in the month of Chislev (aka Kislev) (Nehemiah 1:1-3).', 3, null, null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-10 23:47:22', '<p>Chislev is the 3rd month of the civil calendar or the 9<sup>th</sup> month of the ecclesiastical (sacred) calendar.</p>'),
(241, 1, 0, -502, -502, 'Nehemiah goes before Darius to request permission to rebuild the walls of Jerusalem in the month of Nisan of the 20<sup>th</sup> year of Darius&rsquo; reign (Nehemiah 2:1-10).', 3, null, null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-08 19:59:49', '<p>Nisan is the 7<sup>th</sup> month of the civil calendar or the 1<sup>st</sup> month of the ecclesiastical (sacred) calendar.</p>'),
(242, 1, 0, -502, -502, 'The walls are finished on the 25<sup>th</sup> day of Elul (Nehemiah 6:15).', 3, null, null, null, null, 9, '2021-01-08 22:19:24', '<p>Elul is the 12<sup>th</sup> month of the civil calendar or the 6<sup>th</sup> month of the sacred calendar.</p> <p>The city of Jerusalem is a sacred matter. Therefore the dating of these events are according to the sacred calendar. The repairs to the wall took 52 days (nearly 2 months). Scripture records that the completion of the repairs to the walls were accomplished on the 25<sup>th</sup> day of Elul, the 6<sup>th</sup> month of the sacred calendar. The month of Av is the 5<sup>th</sup> month of the sacred calendar which typically has 30 days. 25 days of Elul plus 27 days of Av (52 days total) makes the repair work beginning around the 3rd day of the month of Av in the 20<sup>th</sup> year of Darius, King of Babylon.</p> <p>The 20<sup>th</sup> year of Darius conincides with the civil year 3460 AH (Tishri through Elul). Since King Darius is a civil matter, his 20<sup>th</sup> year as king is reckoned according to the civil calendar. However the city of Jerusalem is a sacred matter so the months of these events are numbered according to the sacred calendar within the year 3460 AH. Chislev is the 9<sup>th</sup> month of the sacred calendar, however it falls as the 3<sup>rd</sup> month of the civil calendar (this is when the report comes to Nehemiah). Four months later in the 1<sup>st</sup> month of the sacred calendar (which falls as the 7<sup>th</sup> month of the civil calendar (3460 AH) is when Nehemiah makes his request of King Darius. Then 6 months later in the 6<sup>th</sup> month of the sacred calendar which falls as the 12<sup>th</sup> month of the civil calendar (3460 AH) the work on the walls is completed.</p>'),
